================================================================================
MIGRATION SCOPE RECOMMENDATION
================================================================================

RECOMMENDATION: TWO-PHASE MIGRATION (Backend First, Data Deferred)

Key Rationale:
1. INCOMPLETE SOURCE: Only 2 of 4 target tables have source data (50% greenfield)
2. LOW COMPLEXITY: 2 simple tables, no GSIs, minimal attributes
3. RISK REDUCTION: Decouple backend validation (synthetic data) from data migration
4. NO TIME SAVINGS: Single-phase offers no meaningful schedule compression
5. CLEAR ROLLBACK: Two-phase provides clean rollback points at each phase boundary

Phase Breakdown:
- Phase 1 (2-4 weeks): Migrate backend code, validate with synthetic data
- Phase 2 (1-2 weeks): Migrate Franchise & Store data with transformation
- Phase 3 (4-8 weeks): Develop Pet & Order features (greenfield, out of scope)

Total Migration Timeline: 3-6 weeks (excluding Phase 3 greenfield work)
Risk Level: LOW

Detailed justification with technical analysis has been saved to:
    docs/output/data-base-definition.txt
    (See "MIGRATION SCOPE RECOMMENDATION" section)


