================================================================================
LESSONS LEARNED
================================================================================

1. SUPPLEMENTARY SOURCES ARE CRITICAL
   IaC files alone provide insufficient detail for attribute inference. The
   OpenAPI spec (Phase 1 output) and AVP policy schema were essential for
   understanding data relationships and entity structures.

2. "MIGRATION" MAY INCLUDE GREENFIELD WORK
   This project demonstrates that not all target features exist in the source.
   Migration frameworks must distinguish between:
   - Pure migration (source → target transformation)
   - Gap-filling (develop missing features in target)
   - Greenfield (entirely new features with no source analog)

3. AUTHORIZATION IS A FIRST-CLASS CONCERN
   The FaaS application's core complexity is authorization (AVP), not data or
   business logic. Migration planning must prioritize authorization architecture
   decisions early.

4. KEY SCHEMA DESIGN MATTERS
   The petstoreTenants composite key (id + value) is a potential design flaw
   that complicates queries and migration. Evaluate whether legacy key schemas
   should be preserved or refactored during migration.


